<!-- ═══════════════ LESSON 1-3 ═══════════════ -->
<div class="lesson" id="lesson-1-3">
  <div class="lesson-header">
    <div class="lesson-eyebrow">Chapter 1 · The Basics · Lesson 3</div>
    <h2 class="lesson-title">Does the money move instantly?</h2>
    <p class="lesson-lead">Spoiler: no. The payment is approved instantly, but the actual movement of money is a separate process that happens hours later. Here's why.</p>
  </div>

  <h3>Approval and payment are two different things</h3>
  <p>When your card is approved, your bank puts a <strong>hold</strong> on your money — like reserving a parking space. The space is "taken," but you haven't technically paid yet. The actual money moves later in a separate process called <strong>settlement</strong>.</p>

  <div class="box story">
    <span class="box-icon">🏨</span>
    <div>
      <div class="box-title">Hotels do this all the time</div>
      <div class="box-text">When you check into a hotel, they "pre-authorise" your card for a few hundred pounds. You'll see that amount as "pending" in your bank app — but it hasn't been charged yet. At checkout, they charge the actual amount and release the rest. Card payments work the same way: approved first, paid later.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h3>What happens after the approval</h3>
  <p>At the end of the business day, the shop sends all its approved transactions to its bank in one big batch. The bank then sends these to Visa or Mastercard, who calculate the total amounts flowing between all the banks, and then arrange for banks to transfer money to each other. This typically takes one working day.</p>

  <div class="flow-wrap">
    <div class="flow">
      <div class="flow-node lit">
        <span class="flow-node-icon">✅</span>
        <span class="flow-node-name">Approved</span>
        <span class="flow-node-role">Instant — 2 seconds</span>
      </div>
      <div class="flow-arrow">→<div class="flow-arrow-label">then later</div></div>
      <div class="flow-node">
        <span class="flow-node-icon">📦</span>
        <span class="flow-node-name">Batch close</span>
        <span class="flow-node-role">End of day</span>
      </div>
      <div class="flow-arrow">→<div class="flow-arrow-label">next day</div></div>
      <div class="flow-node teal">
        <span class="flow-node-icon">🏦</span>
        <span class="flow-node-name">Settlement</span>
        <span class="flow-node-role">Money moves</span>
      </div>
      <div class="flow-arrow">→<div class="flow-arrow-label">T+1/2</div></div>
      <div class="flow-node lit">
        <span class="flow-node-icon">💰</span>
        <span class="flow-node-name">Shop paid</span>
        <span class="flow-node-role">In their account</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="box insight">
    <span class="box-icon">💡</span>
    <div>
      <div class="box-title">This is why small shops sometimes have cash flow problems</div>
      <div class="box-text">A busy café might process thousands of pounds in payments on a Saturday, but that money doesn't appear in their bank account until Monday or Tuesday. New or higher-risk businesses can wait even longer. Some payment companies offer "instant settlement" — but they charge extra for it, because they're lending the money in the meantime.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="quiz" id="quiz-1-3">
    <div class="quiz-tag">✏️ Quick check</div>
    <div class="quiz-question" id="qq-1-3">You buy a £30 jumper on Saturday afternoon. Your bank shows it as "pending." When does the shop most likely actually receive that £30?</div>
    <div class="quiz-opts" id="qo-1-3">
      <button class="quiz-opt" onclick="answer('1-3',0,2)"><span class="quiz-opt-letter">A</span>Immediately — the approval transfers the money</button>
