<div class="lesson" id="lesson-2-3">
  <div class="lesson-header">
    <div class="lesson-eyebrow">Chapter 2 · Your Card · Lesson 6</div>
    <h2 class="lesson-title">Why do cards get declined?</h2>
    <p class="lesson-lead">It's happened to all of us — that moment of dread when the card reader beeps and says "Declined." Here's what's actually going on behind the scenes.</p>
  </div>

  <h3>Your bank declines, not the shop</h3>
  <p>When a card is declined, it's almost never the shop's fault. The shop's till sent the request to your bank, and your bank said no. The shop can't see why — they just get a code. Sometimes even your bank's app won't show you the exact reason immediately.</p>

  <h3>The most common reasons</h3>

  <table class="tbl">
    <tr><th>What happened</th><th>What to do</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Not enough money or credit available</td><td>Check your balance, use a different card, or pay a smaller amount</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Card reported lost or stolen</td><td>You may have reported it and forgotten — call your bank</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Card expired</td><td>Check the date on the front — you may need your replacement card</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Bank suspects fraud</td><td>Unusual purchase (different country, very large amount) — your bank may have flagged it. They'll often text you to verify.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Daily limit reached</td><td>You've already spent your maximum for the day — wait until midnight or call your bank to increase</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Wrong PIN entered too many times</td><td>Card may be temporarily blocked — use contactless or call your bank</td></tr>
  </table>

  <div class="box good">
    <span class="box-icon">✅</span>
    <div>
      <div class="box-title">What to do when your card is declined in public</div>
      <div class="box-text">Don't panic. Check your banking app immediately — many banks now send instant notifications explaining why. Try a different payment method if you have one. Step aside if there's a queue. Call the number on the back of your card if you're unsure why it happened.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="box insight">
    <span class="box-icon">💡</span>
    <div>
      <div class="box-title">Travelling abroad? Tell your bank first</div>
      <div class="box-text">Banks use patterns to spot fraud — like your card suddenly being used in another country when you were just home. Many banks will block transactions abroad if you haven't told them you're travelling. Most banking apps let you set a travel notification in seconds.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

