<div class="lesson" id="lesson-5-1">
  <div class="lesson-header">
    <div class="lesson-eyebrow">Chapter 5 · The Money Trail · Lesson 11</div>
    <h2 class="lesson-title">What does accepting cards actually cost a shop?</h2>
    <p class="lesson-lead">Card payments aren't free for businesses. Every time you tap, a small slice of your payment goes elsewhere. Here's where it goes — and why.</p>
  </div>

  <h3>The merchant pays a fee on every transaction</h3>
  <p>When you pay £100 in a shop, the shop doesn't keep £100. They pay a percentage called the <strong>Merchant Discount Rate (MDR)</strong> — typically between 0.5% and 2.5% depending on the type of card and the size of the business.</p>

