<!-- 6-1 -->
<div class="lesson" id="lesson-6-1">
  <div class="lesson-header">
    <div class="lesson-eyebrow" style="color:var(--teal)">Module 2 · Intermediate · Chapter 6 · Lesson 13</div>
    <h2 class="lesson-title">How 3DS decides when to ask for proof</h2>
    <p class="lesson-lead">You now know that 3DS is the system that asks you to verify yourself online. But how does it decide when to make your life easy (no interruption) and when to make you enter a code?</p>
  </div>
  <h3>The risk scoring behind the scenes</h3>
  <p>Every time you shop online, your bank's 3DS system receives a package of data about the transaction — not just your card number and the amount, but dozens of signals about the context. It scores all of this to decide: is this risky enough to interrupt the customer?</p>
  <table class="tbl">
    <tr><th>Signal</th><th>Lower risk ✓</th><th>Higher risk ⚠</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Device</td><td>Same phone/laptop you always use</td><td>Unrecognised device</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Location</td><td>Home country, familiar IP address</td><td>Different country from card's BIN</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Merchant</td><td>Site you've bought from before</td><td>First time at this merchant</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Amount</td><td>Similar to your usual spend</td><td>Unusually large purchase</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Time</td><td>Normal hours for you</td><td>3am, unusual pattern</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Velocity</td><td>Normal purchase frequency</td><td>5 transactions in 10 minutes</td></tr>
  </table>
  <div class="box insight">
    <span class="box-icon">💡</span>
    <div>
      <div class="box-title">Two possible outcomes: frictionless or challenge</div>
      <div class="box-text"><strong>Frictionless:</strong> your bank's system is confident it's you — payment goes through silently. You never see a popup. This happens for the majority of trusted, low-value, familiar transactions.<br><br><strong>Challenge:</strong> something looks unusual — your bank asks you to prove it's you. Usually a one-time code by text, a biometric in your banking app, or a push notification to approve.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="box story">
    <span class="box-icon">🎰</span>
    <div>
      <div class="box-title">Your bank is running a probability calculation</div>
      <div class="box-text">Think of it like a bouncer with a mental checklist: "Regular customer? Check. Coming at a normal time? Check. Not acting differently to usual? Check." If everything checks out, you walk in without question. If something feels off, they ask for ID. The 3DS system is doing the same thing, just with dozens of data points in about 200 milliseconds.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="quiz" id="quiz-6-1">
    <div class="quiz-tag">✏️ Knowledge check</div>
    <div class="quiz-question" id="qq-6-1">You're on holiday in Japan and try to buy something online with your UK Mastercard. Which outcome is most likely for 3DS?</div>
