<!-- 8-2 -->
<div class="lesson" id="lesson-8-2">
  <div class="lesson-header">
    <div class="lesson-eyebrow" style="color:var(--teal)">Module 2 · Intermediate · Chapter 8 · Lesson 19</div>
    <h2 class="lesson-title">Velocity rules — catching patterns of fraud</h2>
    <p class="lesson-lead">While ML models handle complex pattern recognition, velocity rules are the simpler, faster first line of defence. They catch fraud that happens in bursts — and they still catch a lot of it.</p>
  </div>
  <h3>What are velocity rules?</h3>
  <p>Velocity rules are threshold-based checks: if a certain thing happens more than X times within a time window, trigger an action. They're simple, fast, and explainable — you can tell exactly why a transaction was blocked.</p>
  <table class="tbl">
    <tr><th>Velocity rule</th><th>What it catches</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Same card used 4+ times in 1 hour</td><td>Rapid testing or scripted fraud attacks</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Same IP used for 3+ different cards in 24 hours</td><td>Automated card testing bots</td></tr>
    <tr><td>5+ transactions under £1 in 10 minutes</td><td>Card enumeration — criminals testing stolen card numbers</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Same device, 3+ cards in 48 hours</td><td>Account takeover or identity fraud</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Spend over £500 in 2 hours (unusual for customer)</td><td>Lost or stolen card being used quickly</td></tr>
  </table>
  <div class="box warning">
    <span class="box-icon">⚠️</span>
    <div>
      <div class="box-title">Velocity rules can catch legitimate customers too</div>
      <div class="box-text">A genuine customer who buys multiple gifts for the same family might trigger a "same address, multiple orders" rule. A developer testing their integration might trigger a "multiple small transactions" rule. Good fraud systems have processes to quickly whitelist legitimate patterns — and customer service teams to handle false positives.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="quiz" id="quiz-8-2">
    <div class="quiz-tag">✏️ Knowledge check</div>
    <div class="quiz-question" id="qq-8-2">A criminal has a list of 500 stolen card numbers. To test which are still active, they make 50p charges to a small website. What velocity rule would most likely catch this?</div>
    <div class="quiz-opts" id="qo-8-2">
