<!-- 12-2 -->
<div class="lesson" id="lesson-12-2">
  <div class="lesson-header">
    <div class="lesson-eyebrow" style="color:var(--gold)">Module 3 · Advanced · Chapter 12 · Lesson 28</div>
    <h2 class="lesson-title">ECI values — what authentication outcomes mean at authorisation</h2>
    <p class="lesson-lead">The Electronic Commerce Indicator (ECI) is a 2-digit code included in the authorisation request after 3DS. It tells the issuer exactly what authentication was performed — and determines who bears fraud liability.</p>
  </div>
  <h3>Visa ECI values</h3>
  <table class="tbl">
    <tr><th>ECI</th><th>Meaning</th><th>Liability</th></tr>
    <tr><td>05</td><td>Fully authenticated — cardholder successfully authenticated (frictionless or challenge)</td><td>Shifts to issuer</td></tr>
    <tr><td>06</td><td>Authentication attempted — 3DS initiated but ACS returned U (unable to authenticate)</td><td>Shifts to issuer</td></tr>
    <tr><td>07</td><td>No authentication — 3DS not attempted, or not applicable (card not enrolled)</td><td>Stays with merchant</td></tr>
  </table>
  <h3>Mastercard ECI values</h3>
  <table class="tbl">
    <tr><th>ECI</th><th>Meaning</th><th>Liability</th></tr>
    <tr><td>02</td><td>Fully authenticated</td><td>Shifts to issuer</td></tr>
    <tr><td>01</td><td>Authentication attempted</td><td>Shifts to issuer</td></tr>
    <tr><td>00</td><td>No authentication</td><td>Stays with merchant</td></tr>
  </table>
  <div class="box insight">
    <span class="box-icon">💡</span>
    <div>
      <div class="box-title">ECI 06/01 (attempted) still shifts liability</div>
      <div class="box-text">Many people don't realise that even a failed or uncompleted 3DS attempt (when the ACS returns U — unable to authenticate) still shifts liability to the issuer, because the merchant made a good-faith attempt. The issuer's system failed to authenticate, not the merchant's. Only ECI 07/00 (no attempt at all) keeps liability with the merchant.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="quiz" id="quiz-12-2">
    <div class="quiz-tag">✏️ Knowledge check</div>
    <div class="quiz-question" id="qq-12-2">A Visa transaction completes with ECI 06. Six months later the cardholder disputes it as fraud. Who bears the chargeback?</div>
    <div class="quiz-opts" id="qo-12-2">
      <button class="quiz-opt" onclick="answer('12-2',0,1)"><span class="quiz-opt-letter">A</span>The merchant — ECI 06 means authentication failed</button>
      <button class="quiz-opt" onclick="answer('12-2',1,1)"><span class="quiz-opt-letter">B</span>The issuer — ECI 06 means authentication was attempted (liability shifts even for attempted auth)</button>
      <button class="quiz-opt" onclick="answer('12-2',2,1)"><span class="quiz-opt-letter">C</span>Visa — they failed to complete authentication</button>
      <button class="quiz-opt" onclick="answer('12-2',3,1)"><span class="quiz-opt-letter">D</span>Split 50/50 between merchant and issuer</button>
    </div>
    <div class="quiz-feedback" id="qfb-12-2"></div>
    <div class="quiz-footer"><span class="quiz-count" id="qc-12-2"></span><span class="quiz-score" id="qs-12-2"></span><button class="quiz-next" id="qn-12-2" onclick="nextQ('12-2')">Next →</button></div>
  </div>
